When the surface temperature drops below the dew point, condensation forms, potentially damaging the filters. To prevent this, an insulated (double-wall) housing is required to maintain the surface temperature above the dew point.
inference_logic: Dew Point Condensation Gate [FIRED]: Monitors Outdoor Condensation

Physics: Outdoor installations cause condensation when surface temperature drops below the dew point. Insulated (double-wall) housing maintains surface temperature above dew point, preventing water damage to filters.

content_segments.text: Additionally, the system is exposed to High Humidity, which accelerates zinc corrosion. The housing corrosion class is C4.
inference_logic: WARNING] Persistent humidity accelerates zinc corrosion, reducing service life. Consider C4 or C5 materials.
Stressor: High Humidity | Relevant trait: Corrosion Resistance C3
